76561198064541161,Recommended,229520,11010075,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,Mr. Gameplay1001,"Dungeon Hearts is one of the most fun, addicting, puzzle/RPG mashup games I've ever played. It's gameplay style is simple, but can quickly turn from being easy to making very quick thinking. You need to match up 3 of the same color circles in order to create a diamond to attack. It gives you something to think about, and strategize as you go further in.The graphics have a nice style to it, but nothing outstanding. One of my favorite parts about this game is the music, ranging from 5 different soundtracks entirely. (Pop, Jazz, Metal, ect)Now the gameplay. These color ruins represent each character, and the grey ruins represents the enemy's attack, or debuff abilities. They travel from the right side of the screen to the left side of the screen. If the color ruins hit the end of left side, any of your ruins will dissappear as well as grey ruins. If an enemy's diamond ruin, or debuff ruin, hits the left end, then it takes effect on which ever character it was heading for.I can go on forever on the gameplay, but it's somewhat simple. I do have a few problems with the game. The difficulty can spike, even on Normal mode. I got half way through the game before I couldn't do anything. It felt like the enemies would take more than 10-15 minutes to defeat if you don't stack the damage. Another thing is that the enemy's don't have a clear health bar. The only way you can tell that an enemy is near defeat is when their ruins begin to crack which can be somewhat annoying. One last thing is the level up system. It is a minor nickpick, but I don't consider it all that bad. You must match 3 color star ruins in order to level up. Fail to do so will result in low level characters, and some challenging enemies.Overall I think this game is fantastic with amazing music, and quick thinking puzzling, RPG, gameplay. It's just very nice to play this game and it puts me in a relaxed mood in the beginning to becoming intense in the later part of the game. I give it an 8/10."
